text: <@U05D5QEBWS3> 0.7.9 of `cms-dev-server` should cover both of these

Is there documentation on js module meta config options, or js object shape at parity with hubl json shape options? e.g.
```{
  label: 'Card',
  global: false,
  host_template_types: ['PAGE'],
  is_available_for_new_content: true,
  ...
}```
vs.
```{
  "label" : "Card",
  "global" : false,
  "host_template_types" : [ "PAGE" ],
  "is_available_for_new_content" : true
  ...
}```
It is a JS object with parity for HubL module meta.json (as described in <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/building-blocks/modules/configuration>)
